description: Easy on the roads. Happy new years all, may it bring more races than the last one!

4*2mins + 4*1min hills.

Wee hill session on the path up from Beck Wythop. Felt fine, don't think GPS is very accurate up there but was moving okay.  Good work.
Easy round the block. Nice and icy and dark to keep things spicy. Stayed upright which was a bonus.

Sale fell, whythop woods and the Bass trail with Spender, couldn't ask for anything more ❤. Path up Sale fell was lethal, just fully ice so had to bosh beside it, apart from that was all decent running. Finished with another wee loop solo to take it to 90mins, good week done, onto an easier one.
Jog up Slate Fell with Niamh. Very nice and chill, good start to easy week.

"Threshy" ints - 6*4mins[1min]

On the low road, was still a bit icy but didn't notice it that much. The roundabout was fun each rep, but fine, just had to keep my wits about me. Ran too fast but I still felt real comfy, HR high tho. Anyways stopped at 6 instead of 8 coz I don't want a big effort in the legs, hopefully will go and do the Whinlatter TT on Saturday, so want to be fresh for that. New shoes feeling good.
Round the block. It was icy as fook.
Easy Binsey terrain loop. Felt alright, right foot pretty tight tho.
Pootle round the block. Ice fine, nowhere near like yesterday. Forgot HRM, but blaring tunes was an excellent substitute.

Along bass trail, up steeeeep Barf track, then through the forest onto Lords Seat, along the skyline, then cut across the big bog to Ling fell, down and back over the side of Sale. Nice route, enjoyed it a lot. Snowy and low vis on the ridge made it good fun.
Snow running :) much nicer than ice.

Little man and Lonscale fell. Winter conditions with some mega drifts at the top which was fun, deep enough to be able to just run over a fence at one point. Was running at a good pace up the main track and actually ran quicker than during the GB mountain running champs in 2018, with a much lower effort so fitness it definitely in a good place. Enjoyed it a lot, will get into the hills more often.
Murthy with spender, bit bloody icey in places.
Easy post S&C over to Blindcrake and back via the road. Weather not too nice, and fields were nice and muddy.
We supposedly had performance core at 9am, but that never happened. Did it anyways coz had already planned the day like that.
Jog round the block, got heavily rained on. Need to lose some bunda atm hehe.
Lovely morning, cold and still. Grew nicely into the yog, legs feeling awake at the end :)
Threshy with Dan.
Easy Murthy, was meant to be 70' but I'd underestimated the muddiness of the forest. Anyways really good fun, if a little wet.
After a sweet nap.

STEADY with Dan. I do enjoy these runs where you can just roll along, definitely much easier to do with spender rather than solo. Good chat, and only one poo break, which actually I had nothing to do with (!!). A very enjoyable outing.
Have got a lactate measurer, which read 11.3 post run, which I am very much not convinced about, so I probably need to set it up correctly.

Late getting up today coz I watched Gladiator last night, good film. Anyways a nice easy run round the block, quite icy out but deceptively icy as I found out when I tried to turn around and decked it quite hard. Knees grazed, but we'll survive. Beaut morning tho and felt alright :)
Round the block recovery. Snuck it in before it got dark.

Power Hills with Dan. 6*60s + 4*30s.

Full of lactic, pretty grim stuff. Glad of the company.
PASTA PLS

Mountains with spendog. Up Ullock ridge, then up Skidaw, down to Skidaw Littleman, then cut back to Carlside and down to Dodd and back through the woods. A two poop, two pee run today. Very cold and icy at the top, nice Arctic conditions and took a very suspect line at one point which required a bearing and some faith, nearly slid a long long way down a couple frozen snow patches but we made it out alive. Great fun, would repeat.
Easy roads. HR pretty low for some reason.
Recovery roads.
EUOC core.

Terrain ints - 7*6mins[90s].

A new one for me, doing a session in terrain. The loop we did was pretty good, had some grassy (boggy) path sections, a few cut through between these through the woods, and then a bit of a gravel track as well, with varying hillyness throughout. Definitely felt like a more muscular session then threshy ints I've previously done, and you could really notice the change in running style/ aggression when needing to push through the forest. Very much appreciated having spender to run with, would have been a grim grim day without him. All in all very good fun, and time flew by, didn't feel like that long at all, will hopefully do this again!
private note: Lac 6.2, hmm?

description: Proper plod. Just needed to move the muscles.
56 controls on Aughertree fell. Good times.
Trying to actually find the pit at 1; it was tiny.

Big ooft round Whinlatter with Spender. Hills were a bit grindy but I enjoyed it nonetheless. Snowy at the highest point which got a bit slippy in road shoes, but mostly just nice gravel tracks. Good chat as always. Got back to a Uni email saying it'll all be online this semester, so looks like the Spud x Spender training camp will continue a wee while longer.
Easy. Followed by 2hrs of building a deer fence which was tough work.
Yoge.
EUOC core.

Road reps - 8*3mins[90s]

Paces: 3.17, 16, 15, 13, 12, 14, 11, 02

With Spendog on the low road heading out of Cockermouth. Odd reps ever so slightly downhill, even reps slightly up but basically flat. A bit icy but the pavement actually turned out to be pretty okay, the only issue was there was a big section of pavement roadworks which forced us onto the road which was actually mega slippy. Realised after a few reps we could just dodge round it tho and get back on the pavement pretty quickly, so not ideal but not too much of an issue.

Anyways legs felt quite alright, and very pleased to find that pace pretty comfy, which is nice considering I haven't dropped sub 3.30s in a few months... I was wearing Saucony endorphin speed, not a carbon plate shoe but the training version, reckon it did help a bit as I only felt strained on the last rep really. 

Whatever it was, the session was a good reminder to the spudingtons of how to run fastish again.
Yog. Binned the shoes afterwards, onto destroying another pair!
In the snowy fells with Spendog on a glorious day. Bloody marvelous.
Easy. Legs feeling surprisingly very good this morning so was rolling nicely. I reckon it was the Ronhills that did it.
Plod.
Not EUOC core coz I had a presentation at 5.

Rugby Pitches Threshy - 2*10mins + 4*5mins.

With Spendog. Bit muddy but really not too bad. Felt fine, nothing special just getting it done.
Skog munchers do strides; a funny sight.
Jog.
Easy lope round Setmurthy. Cloudy on the Hay which was cool. Feeling very bog standard.
Core n dat.

Sale Fell Orienteering.

Run in a okay speed, raz pace, so the mind was focused but it wasn't too much hard work. Really enjoyed it, man I love this sport :)
Easy on roads. Feeling pretty good :)
Plod post core.
Dub.
Pre hills tempo out along the old main road from Beck Whythop to Powter How and back. Drag of a hill into headwind on the way out, much nicer on the way back.

6*60s + 6*30s.

Just up the forest track. Moving fine, made sure to keep decent form the whole way instead of trying to fight the lactic near the end of reps.
Up in da fells cutting some rogue lines. Brilliant fun but bloody cold up top.

Easy ont roads. Misjudged it so had to run around the garden for 4mins at the end to get to 50mins. Legs feeling all normal :)

Mixing up the week slightly so that'll be all for today.
Early so I could cook tea :0

Long time no 3/4 baggies and long socks combo, so fixed that one today :) Anyways 7*6mins[90s] terrain ints with spendog up in the wood. A nice layer of snow, which we'd churned into mud by the end of the session. Tough work as per but felt good for it.
Round the block. Cold and wet out which made this not pleasant. Still I always appreciate the thinking time :)

Faulds Brow Otek. Crikey, I haven't got that cold in a good while, a good reminder to always wear more than needed, and a waterproof today wouldn't have done any harm either. Anyways tough going up on the fell with a good layer of snow on the ground, and then even tougher when the snow/sleet started, yikes.
Tekkers okay, but compass didn't seem overly accurate, maybe that can be put down to the old map and magnetic north moving?? Anyways technique was fine tbh, and good terrain time so aye, decent days work.
Ate my yeetabix for brekky and off I went. Bit of a hill in the middle but was nice to get rolling on the way back. Bass trail pretty muddy actually.

Jog with 4*30s hill sprints thrown in. Been bouncing around the house this afternoon after munching a whole big bar of choccy, unsurprisingly felt shite on the run, but the legs felt good. Do need to sort my eating out, i do try but it's hard, in fact I'd go so far as saying its the hardest thing about training for me personally.
The hill sprints.
Jog round the Murthy. Mother was going shopping in town so took the opportunity to get a different perspective on things. Muddy muddy pretty much everywhere atm.

Road sesh - 4*(3',2',1') 1min between everything.

Needed a poop for the whole thing which wasn't ideal but we made it through. Physically (apart from the poop) not feeling amazing tbh but didn't really push it so got through fine and paces looked fine, everything sub 3.10s (apart from 3.12s first rep).

I'm currently about about 3kg over racing weight which is fine for winter season but ideally I'd like to be training at 68-69kg not the big 70kg I am atm. However the past few weeks have been a big training load, more than I've ever done before so I'd rather have too much fuel in the tank than too little. But I can definitely feel the extra weight, especially when doing sessions (this could be a placebo effect tho I'm fairly sure it's not) so I'll try to eat a bit more normally in the coming weeks rather than just literally everything within sight which is what happens atm (again not a bad thing when training hard!)
Jog after a terrible game of rugby ;)

Fells avec Dan. Some nice rocky ones today which made the descents pretty slow and tekky. Was clear up top as well but really blummin cold. Lovely to be out in the hills anyways, another good week in da bag, time for an easier week.
First rest day in a while, can't say I enjoyed it that much.

Rugby Pitches Threshy - 2*9'[2'] + 4'.

Smol sesh for an easy week. Just keeping it chill. Was a beaut of a day, firm frozen ground and blue skies. Bit of a cold wind but generally very nice.
4 strides.
Getting me plod on. Very clear evening ❤
Easy round Sale Fell. Legs feeling okay and lovely weather so very much enjoyed it.

Scale Hill Course courtesy of Nixon. Taken at a good pace. Very much enjoyed it, area was tough, as was the planning but I orienteered well so was a good mornings work. HR is from the wrist, so not massively accurate but looks about right.
Plod with 4*30s flat at the end to try and un-skog the legs. Should probably have done like 15s as these felt more like reps than strides.
Jog on roads. Legs just feeling a bit meh, but what can ya do eh.

A lap of Grasmoor. Wind was ridiculous today, was sat in the car beforehand and the car was shaking so didn't really wanna get out. Decided to stay off the tops and stick to the valleys but I reckon it was just as bad coz all the wind was being funnelled through them. Took a rogue rogue descent to get off the ridge which was scarily windy. No session as I wasn't feeling at my best, plus into this wind it would've been pointless. Easy week anyways so no harm done, will get back to it next week.
Jog round the block. Wore many clothes and played music outloud, so I was warm and entertained.
Romp round the Whinlatter fireroads with Spenny. Good chat and time went by quickly, wind wasn't that bad either in the shelter of the woods :)
Easy on the roads. Wearing way too many layers.

14.06 km (25.4 kph) +219m. What's this, a bike ride?! Took the opportunity of the "warm" weather to dust the old steed off for the first time in a few months. Enjoyed it, although the wind was still there so that was unpleasant. Might do a bit of riding every now and then, weather and tiredness permitting.

12mins, 9mins, 6mins, 4*3mins.

Avec Dan on the pitches which have softened up in the great thaw, so a bit muddy, however it was the wind which was very grim today. Legs not feeling brilliant but we made it though. Onto the next.
Ploddington round the block on a beautifully calm evening. 4*15s at the end and this time the legs felt better for it :)
Jog out up Rannerdale and back with Dan.
Scale Hill forest sprint. Good fun pinging about on a 1:4000 map.

12.7 km (22.9 kph) +244m.
Gentle ride out, quite enjoyed it :)

5 * 6mins [1min] threshy.

Reps around 3.30s, varying either side. Legs feeling fine, just smooth rolling which was nice. Bit of wind but generally not too bad. Just experimenting with another light Thursday session, legs felt just as good at the end as at the start, but real test will be how they feel at the weekend, will probably just bang a steady again next Thursday, will play it live.
Jog with 4*15s hills. Felt good.
Jog on the roads in some nasty weather. Just glad to get it done!

Honister Middle - Map Wet and windy, but not too cold thankfully. Proper grimey up on the top section but fine down in the valley. Anyways I tried to just focus on the nav, which was okay but I struggled with the map at points, especially which boulders had been mapped and which hadn't (for example at #2 and #5, there were lots of boulders on the ground and no obvious one which was on the map) An okay start to faster orienteering, but lots of work to do!
Proper plod. Not much rain but much more wind.
Coledale Horseshoe with an extension up Grasmoor. Mr Spencer wasn't messing about today so harder than usual, all good fun tho and so nice to be in the fells in good weather again.
Just ran at the pace the legs gave me. After yesterday, that wasn't too fast! Also lovely weather.

15.87 km (23.7 kph) +305m.

Beaut afternoon so would have been rude not to.

Round the murthy, hiding in the trees from the wind and rain. Feeling okay, but legs wouldn't have been ready for a session today and with these winds it would've been grim anyways. Will hopefully bang it out tomorrow.
Jog. Horrendous weather.

Tempo on the Keswick -> Threlkeld railway line. Slightly uphill on the way out, then a lovely slight downhill on the way back. Went here coz I hoped the wind and rain wouldn't be too bad in the valley and I was pleasantly surprised that conditions were quite good, still raining and breezy but neither effected running much. Felt fine, never had to push it, except the last few minutes coz why not. Good job done.
Slooooow.
Standard fell orienteering at Mosser just keeping the tekkers live. Weather was very nice, felt almost like spring, and legs feeling alright as well so a good mornings training.
Jog jog plod plod.
Ate a fish finger mid way through to keep spirits high.
Easy on the roads. Feeling fine.

17.26 km (25.1 kph) +291m.

Beaut evening ride.

Ling fell Oints with Dan.

4 courses, each starting with a ~4min climb to the cairn at the top then straight into the full gas downhill course. Pretty savage session tbh, deep in the red by the top (except last rep which we jogged up) each time then had to get the head in gear for some sub 4s downhill O. Dan did a classic 180 off the top on rep 3 which was amusing but also highlighted to me how much less aggressive I orienteered when I wasn't racing someone directly. Something I've worked on a lot this past year but could always still be better.

Rest of the courses were goood tho, on the last one I messed about trying to find a pretty non-existent crag when I was clearly in the circle, should have just done a GG and air-punched it and kept going coz then Dan caught back up so was a grim finish to the rep. All in all very good fun, beaut day felt like summer, so yea enjoyed highly.
Jog on roads. Feeling g.
Quality run in the Loweswater fells, shorts and t-shirt weather which was very much appreciated.

Wow what a stressy morning. Have a project due at 1600 today, which I just couldn't figure out one question for. Anyways this lead to a bad sleep and I woke up at like 5.30am with maths yeeting round the head so got up and actually managed to solve it before 7am. Quite relieved but also quite annoying cos I spent all of Friday trying to do it. Anyways after that I was fugged so went back to sleep till 11, then got up and out for this run.

23.89 km (24.0 kph) +431m.

Back from the run, proof read and submitted then straight back out into the glorious sunshine on the bike.

Rugby Pitches - 9*4mins[1min] avec spendog.

Noice light wan, legs didn't feel amazing but moving fine. Dans watch getting significantly faster paces as per but what can ya do eh. Also my HR seems ~5bmp lower than usual, probably a combination of being tired, being fit and the HRM uncertainty. Hopefully more of the 2nd one ;)
4*15s. Celebration practise haha.

Jog up Lords Seat, then a few controls back down. Forgot how deep the heather is up at the top but that was only bad for a few minutes. Weather was unreal above like 400m, proper summer vibes, in complete contrast to below this which was freezing cloud, made for a nice view at the top.
Yog round da block. Felt fine.

Mawbray course from last summer.
Ngl thought I was fully sending that but clearly not, legs tired. I remember similar feels from the Portugal camp last year, when I went full ham on a night chase and got the HR to like 156 avg. Both times I felt like I was going at racing speed, but actually could be moving a whole lot faster, kinda both annoying and exciting.
Nav was on the whole very good today, with a few little things which could be sharpened, as always.
Won't be doing a session till next Wednesday now, so hopefully the spudingtons come back to life.
Run on the roads. Feeling alright, legs a bit tired on the hills.
3 core sets before tea. Saving the cycle for some extra height tomorrow!

Big send in da fells with Spendog. My boi wasn't messing about, especially on the second long climb so I just tucked in and grinded on up. Mega rouge route off the Whiteside ridge, but all good fun. Am not convinced I'll get out for a ride this afternoon, but we'll see!

Skiddaw * 2 and Great Calva. Amazing day, enjoyed that so so much, just messing about in the hills with Dan. Topped off with a bounty stop and a full send down a big scree, lovely. More like this plz!

24.74 km (17.9 kph) +732m.

Out with ma bois Dan and Breeze for the final push. Got a sense of achievement which I haven't felt since JWOC when we did it, so despite the big physical effort of this weekend I'd say the psychological benefits majorly outweigh this. Also we raised a shit ton of money for the mountain rescue so yea a good job well done :)
Taking the rest day for obvious reasons. Was quite tired this afternoon, but perked up now :)
Easy bass trail. Bog standard stuff, legs feeling very very average.
Dub

4 * 7mins [2mins] + 4 * 2mins [1min].

Threshy work on the Keswick railway. Rainy day and legs feeling pretty standard so just getting it put away. Onto the next :)
Pootle round the block. Think God's sent a plague of frogs to Sunderland, must have seen at least 20 of them crossing the road.
Mooch about Sale fell and Ling fell. Pretty windy up top but I felt alright and the sun was shining for the majority so a good run.
private note: Wrist HR.

description: Pootle round da block.
Easy round the block. Nothing to report.
Same but slower. Post core.

Hills - 12*1min + 6*30s.

Jog down recovery on all of them. Felt fine, just ticking them off. Got joined by a dog in last 1min rep which was not ideal for me, the dog, or the dogs owner, but hey ho was good entertainment. 30s were pretty grim but felt like good honest work. Onwards we go!
Bumped into spendog and had a chat.
Haven't been fully soaked for a wee while so this was refreshing. Felt decent.

Hiding in the woods of Whinlatter from the weather. With Dan, just rolling along nicely with good chat for the majority, so an enjoyable one. Managed to cultivate some horrendous DOMs  in ma bum from yesterday so they were sore throughout but we roll with the punches and move forward, as always. Good mornings work.

20.97 km (23.8 kph) +387m.

Spin round the valley of peace. (Sunderland -> Blindcrake -> Redmain -> Bridekirk -> Cockermouth -> Isel -> Sunderland)
"If you only do what you can do, you'll never be better than what you are" - master shifu; kung fu panda 1, quite probably my favourite film.
Bucket hat time, paying my respects to the father for his birthday.
Whilst in a tutorial; new level unlocked.
Visited the Lidl of mileage shops today and purchased 14 dirt cheap bones. Felt fine, and a lovely spring day as well so a good run all round.
Pootle round the block. Proper red sky sunset which was v good v nice.

3 * Sale Fell. Taken at a decent pace, nothing crazy, probably around threshy. Had planned 4 but the legs didn't want another, so stuck with 3 quite happily. 8.33, 31, 37 for each climb and a jog down in between. Noice. (Last did this session in 2016)
Jog, you guessed it, round the block on the roads.

O-tek up on High Doat. Weather was quality, some big summer vibes. Technique was okay, but still some work to do before the hotly contested WCOC Thursday evening series starts in a few weeks, canny wait! Haha.
East money.
Run round the Whythop woods. Lovely big gravel tracks the whole way, legs feeling bang average, and decent weather. Will take that combo any-day :)
Jog round some grassy places in Cockermouth, before picking up fish and chips for tea, yum yum.

20 * 300m starting every 2mins.

Down at the Maryport Harbour which actually turned out to be a very good place for this session coz the road had a big cycle lane/ parking section on the side so despite there being a few cars about I could stay off the pavement away from walkers (eww walking) and also not get run over. Measured the 300m twice on the WU and it ended up being between two speed bumps so I just ran that each time. Even reps (coming back) had a headwind but for the coast it was fine. Legs felt fine although moving that fast didn't feel great, just not used to it at all. Overall a successful session.
To le start.
Back.

Some good marsh munching with Dan on Armboth fell. After a bit of an overshoot early on (which was very much my fault) but after this we got much better, and was interesting to see the different micro lines being run. I enjoyed it very muchos, want more training like this, ideally with this weather as well :)

25.14 km (24.7 kph) +408m.

Spin down to Cockermouth, then to Embleton and Bass lake and then back via Isel Bridge. Bit chilly out today but dry and not much wind so pretty nice cycling conditions. Enjoyed it, legs feeling a bit tired tho.
Bass track miles. An accidental progression of sorts, feeling fine.
Jog.

4*8mins[2mins] + 2*4mins[1min] the EUOC session ran like a pollard float session, confusing stuff.

Ran on the Thirlmere Road which is a class place to session like this, flat, basically no cars (I think 1 came past me), no people about and nice views, so yea I had a good time out there. Bit of a headwind at points, seemingly in random directions but it didn't affect the running much. Felt pretty fine, paces decent, good one done :)
Not pleasant weather tbh. Snuck into a field for some lovely soft ground.
Skog munch at Lodore. Pretty wet and pretty slippy but pretty enjoyable as well. Tekkers g.
Jog, windy windy out there.
Legs feeling actually decent today which was nice, so had a good roll around whinlatter :)
Pootle round da block. Legs once again feeling g, so this wasn't the usual 5.20s :)

2km T, (4*60s + 4*45s + 4*30s + 4*15s) hills, 2km T.

Tempo on the Bass trail, so not the fastest place (party due to dodgy af GPS on it) and also it's single track which caused some issue with passing other people. Hills where I did them 2weeks ago, on a big forest track. Overall I actually felt rather good and the hills especially went well :) Next week should be able to run with other people for the sessions :0
Another training day wrapped up with a jog round the block.

Fug me that was grim. Legs felt like a bag of potato's and calfs nice and tight throughout. Big slog up through a marsh onto Lords Seat, then got bent backwards by some nice horizontal rain for about 10mins, before I'd had enough and bailed off the hill. The sections in the woods were enjoyable but was a big mistake to go up high today, ah well, got it done and another week ticked.
Jog round the block. Too wet and windy for cycling today so will leave it at this.
Grassy miles in Cockermouth.
Glorious sunshine for a jog round the block. On a more serious note I still haven't had a poop today, concerning stuff.

Uphill tempo on Skiddaw avec Spendog.
Had a bit of a false start when ~30s in I realised the path we were on wasn't where I thought we where, but we decided to plough on anyways. Said path turned into not much of a path very quickly but we'd committed and it was going in an upwards direction which is all that mattered. It lead back to the main track after ~10mins and after that it was just a big ol grind on up the hill. Effort was at a good level, so quite spangled by the top, had a sit down for a wee while. Good work banked.
No double today, hit the 90mins this morning so no need. Standard s&c jobbo.
Jog round the block. Leggies actually feeling good despite yesterday. Sunny but quite a cold wind. WCOC event this afternoon :)))

WCOC event @ Crag Hills - Map Some nice lumpy bumpy limestone fields, not tricky but still fun. Have missed that sweet SI air noise and finding the little orange and white things, so was enjoying myself muchos. Lovely evening as well :)

Legs had no right to feel good this morning, but here we are with a lovely run round Derwent water in the sunshine and spudingtons which felt very nice. Feel like I haven't hit a proper plod in a while, will make sure to get one in this afternoon.
Nice lil pootle round the block. Sunny business :)

10*400m[1min], 4mins rest, 10*200m[1min].

Nice one down at the Whitehaven track, just 3 other people using the track so nice and quiet and two of the other guys are long distance runners so should be able to jump in with their sessions for the next few weeks hopefully. Times were

70, 69, 68, 69, 69, 68, 68, 68, 68, 66,
31, 30, 30, 30, 31, 30, 31, 30, 31, 29.

Legs feeling the short rest quite badly on the last few 200s, abso swimming down the home straight on the last one haha. Should defo get some spikey bois coz was all over the place in these shoes, especially noticeable on the bends of the 200s. Good session done.
Plod on.

BOC Long 2012 re-run - Map (soz bout the quality) Found all the old maps at home (mum organised) so jumped at the chance for some 1:15000 properly printed training. With Dan, moving at an okay pace and nav was sound for the vast majority. Enjoyed myself muchos.
Need to actually do something on a rest day coz despite all the extra time I've done pretty much fug all.
O-tek at Jaws - Map Quite a rocky area, but I was moving okay. Technique grand.
Shuffle back to car.

Bailed session. Mainly coz I crunched my ankle on the second rep, but also head and legs weren't in it today :( Can't believe I managed to do the ankle on a track, albeit a pretty rough dirt track (which is very much not 400m). Pretty frustrated with myself, need to get the head in the game.
Jog, ankle good, will just be a bit sore for ~1week I estimate.
Easy round the Wythop woods. On the big tracks for the ankle, which was more stiff than I'd anticipated this morning but pretty fine to run on.
Little jog round the WCOC event at Allonby. Ankle surprisingly really g.
Easy on roads. Legs feeling good and no pain from the ankle (which would expect on roads). It was a bit stiff this morning but nicely loosened off by the end of the run, good signs indeed.
The block.

3 * ~3km courses @ Blakeholme.

Mass start with Dan for the first two. One big wobble on the first one, and another on the last one. Apart from that good nav. Speed through the terrain was decent, ankle a bit sore on the first one so wasn't pushing through the rough sections well, second course went much better because the ankle felt fine and nav good and ran very hard. Third one legs a bit tired but still a good effort. Messed up the 2nd control on this loop so stopped and had a restart, much better after that, and good speed. Lots to work on but a good start to fast O season!
Forest in quality condtions, so lush.
Shadowing NWJS juniors.

SYO event @ Tankersley - Results Big old day on the driving front, but all worth it to find some flags. Went pretty hard and the nav was okay. About mid way round I took a hefty tumble which knocked the wind outta me, and I wasn't running as fast after that. However I was catching an SYO man (which I later found out to be Oli Johnson, lol, the long hair threw me) but he was moving very well so the pace ramped back up to get the catch. Had to deploy some cheeky corner cuts to pass him but after that I orienteered very well in full spud speed mode till the finish. Great fun tbh, lots of paths but I actually find these sorta areas harder than deep skog, so pleased to keep it clean. More pls.
Bonked so hard.

24.06 km (24.5 kph) +488m.

Lovely spin in the sunshine. Forgot to say yesterday but ankle pretty much back to normal now, was just a good reminder to keep doing the exercises and to warm them up properly before training.
Jiggle round the block.
Jog at Whinlatter. Felt like shite this morning.
Jog round the block, still feeling a bit ropey.

EUOC seshwan - 6*3mins[2mins] + 6*30s[1min].

Paces: 3.12, 04, 02, 02, 01, 2.59s.

Solo jobbo today, down on Low Road in Cockermouth. Felt fine, took the first rep to get into it as per then hitting some decent paces for me. Pretty happy to sneak the sub 3s on the last rep, think that's a first sub3 km in a session for myself :)

LOC Middle race @ Bell Wood - Map / Results *just the run-in away from a superman, grr haha Legs felt fine tbh, lacking somewhat in the uphills but not too bad. Area was proper rocky anyways so running speed was more limited by that than the legs. Nav was good. Highlight of the evening was garotting my shin on a one wire waist high fence. I saw it too late, tried to jump it but the shin didn't make it, hence a rather comical head over heels job. Do need to watch out for fences in the future!
Plod round the block pre brekky. Nice morning but got not much time for the pre brekky grind.
Up Burnbanks beforehand.

WCOC event @ Fangs Brow.

What a classic area, some good old fields then some open fell. Enjoyed my run around with Sunley following pretty much the whole way ;)
Bass trail + some road. Leggies felt fine so some smooth rolling.
Round the block to end another dag.
3 courses at Graythwaite, hijacking the Talent squad training (cheers RichT). Nav okay but made two small mistakes in the green, all good learning. Tough stuff as per.
Shadowing until the ankle got a wee tweak, called it a day then.

Newland fells. Felt actually pretty g so was having a grand old time. "You look so light coming up here" was a comment made by a walker, quite potentially the only time I'll every be described as light so I'll take it haha.
Spin out to Aughertree and back. Hillier than I expected but all good fun, and another nice day made it very enjoyable indeed.
Round the block. Tired quads probably from fells yesterday and cycle this morning, so went slow.

Setmurthy. The forestry wombles have blocked off all the main paths, and someone else has blocked off stiles out of the woods, so all in all I wasn't very impressed. However it was a nice warm day and the Hay still provided the goods, so can't be too upset.
Round the block. Flies in yer face.

8 * 2mins [90s].

Down on Low Road with Dan, although his legs are still in Bob Graham mode so he was a bit behind, still much nicer than doing it solo, gives someone to suffer with. My legs didn't feel brill, but good enough to get through it fine, only really hurt on the final rep. Reps from 3.13 -> 2.58 with avg 3.03. Not too bad.
Aughertree O-tek. Good stuff, still struggle with the map in places but the majority was good stuffs.
Jog on the rugby pitches whilst the fam orienteered.
Easy in the Whythop woods. Lovely sunny morning.
Pootle round Keswick.
Beck Pane Forest Sprint - Map Full send in some peng woods. Legs providing the goods and nav pretty spot on, so a very enjoyable morning.
5 * ~40s hills in terrain. Got a Galoppen tomorrow so no need to do much (/any) volume in the session today.
Jog in Cockermouth.

Note to self; when you wake up and can't walk due to pain, it's best to not attempt to run :)

Yesterday hurt my foot somehow, I think just landing on a rock badly (ran on at the time) anyways yesterday afternoons jog was fairly painful, but this morning was more sore, so this run was not very pleasant.
Less painful.

Also less painful until I stood on a rock (who would have guessed that would happen in orienteering) then into a whole world of pain, couldn't hack it anymore so sacked it in. Just gotta play it live for a bit.

First exam completo, day off to let stuff settle. All in all a fairly relaxing day I must say, will probably do some cycles the next few days then see what foots doing. As of today walking was all good and a wee jog about the living room feels fine so pretty happy tbh, back on the mileage in no time.

58.6 km (26.5 kph) +1109m.

Double Whinlatter jobbo. All good fun and I felt OK, legs just getting used to the cycling grind again. Forgot how sweet the descent is down the Keswick side, proper moto GP style cornering. Also saw a campervan hearse (funeral coffin car thing) which seems quite weird to me, but whatever floats ur boat I guess.

55.88 km (24.9 kph) +888m.

Took it more chill today, except when I ran out of gears going up Newlands pass had to grind that one out. Do need to fix the gears on the back coz atm I top out at a 23t, since it won't shift into the 25t (which is also arguably a bit small). Anyways I got over the pass just about. Nasty headwind the whole way home but got it done. Also bloody freezing!
Ate muchos birthday choccy so feeling a bit ropey haha.

61.03 km (26.1 kph) +1080m.

Lap of the Northern fells, when I was coming through Mungrisedale could see the wall of shite weather that I was riding towards, and sure enough I proceded to get fucked on by hail and rain for 30mins, all whilst riding into a headwind. Fair to say I was not loving life at that moment. Couldn't feel my feet or hands for rest of the ride but we made it home only to endure that horrible tingling pain as everything warms back up too quickly. Anyways back to revision, fml.
Test jog, first half with spenny hyping him up for his big show down with Sunley. Foot feeling good.
Easy on roads with 6*1min[1min] mostly uphill. Foot defo noticeable, gotta play it live.

31.55 km (20.6 kph) +599m.

Took the mother's bike out for some gravel riding, it's a big old hybrid commuter bike but held firm on the rough tracks, which is all that's needed. Actually proper good fun, have been considering purchasing a gravel bike for a while, maybe the time is right...!!

25.73 km (24.6 kph) +477m.

Lil easy one pre exam.
Second exam done, went to the pub afterwards, noice.

78.29 km (26.6 kph) +1522m.

Had pondered a 100km job but couldn't really be sacked, especially when it started raining as I started the ride, but I probably could have and the weather turned out okay, ah well. Anyways, down to Lorton, then up Whinlatter, round Derwent water taking in the Ashness Bridge climb, and then back home. Went all the way up to Watendlath on the Ashness Bridge climb, then on the way back down stopped at surprise view for a bar and well, a view. Took both the climbs somewhat hard, it's pretty much impossible to not go hard on these climbs when I have fuck all gear choice, need to sort that, as I reckon Honister and Newlands are probably impossible on my bike atm. Nice ride tbh.

Was gonna cycle but it was pissing it down all day and there was no way I could be sacked with 90mins of that. Tried to purchase a decent turbo this afternoon on Facebook but the negotiations fell through (think I offered a bit low lol) so I'll be relying on Mr amazon to supply the goods asap.

43.44 km (26.3 kph) +740m.

The four Elva Hill climbs, nice short efforts with each being 2-4mins long so was just going full gas up them. Legs felt decent, but body not feeling great. Then onto Keswick for some shopping with the mother. Got rained on going to Keswick so feet ended up with no feeling.
On the old turbo coz it was pissing it down outside. Hopefully the last time coz it's pretty terrible, new one comes tomorrow :)

28.84 km (23.1 kph) +670m.

Shit just ain't going right atm. Freehub broke at about 50mins, so the bike was turned into a fixie (have to always pedal), shame coz it was a beaut day as well and had planned a lot more.
Inside watching River Monsters whilst it hailed outside, new turbo was a good purchase.

Rode hard on the turbo for an hour. Was sweating so much, could ring my tits out like a soggy sponge by the end, and lost 2kg. Watched Tour de Romandie highlights and the giro preview, might have to purchase eurosport or something to watch that.

33.93 km (20.9 kph) +735m.

Some more road / very much not road combo. At one point I ended up on a downhill mountain bike track which I crept down at about 3kph, fat road tires not doing bits there. Hailed on twice but I actually had the right amount of clothes on and kinda enjoyed it in a weird way, defo much nicer when ur not freezing.

19.98 km (21.3 kph) +354m.

Some new bits of farm tracks and one big field. Lovely morning.
Getting huge
En timme på turbo. Not that sweaty, watched tour de France 2018 highlights, good stuff.

3 * 8mins [2mins].

Watching the giro tt (on GCN+), basically one 8mins interval was someone's race so that worked out quite nicely.

11.19 km (24.3 kph) +124m.

Puncture. Phoned mummy to bail me out x
Turbo with the giro, went for a couple of the sprints with them, I reckon I'd have had it ;)
Spin. Taking an easy easy week. Probably try the return to running next week.
3 * 10mins [2mins]. Timed it to be with the end of the giro stage, suffered along with them.

28.87 km (24.4 kph) +520m

Fixed most of the road bike. New rear wheel, cassette (so I actually have some easy gears for the hills now), and brake pads. Bottom bracket is wobbling so that needs replaced at some point, a job for another day me thinks. Lovely to train outside again :0

Starting my transition to Ski-O athlete haha. Rollerski on the Thirlmere road with big Herbie, I thought he was gonna teach me but as it turned out he was as shit as I was ;) we got into at the end tho. Might try the Keswick railway with the nice tarmac, get some speed on the go. Having said that the one bit of downhill there was I crashed pretty much instantly, luckily I've muchos bunda to cushion my fall.
Good fun, would be nice to get to the point where I could consider it proper aerobic exercise, which it basically was nearer the end.

31.39 km (31.7 kph) +446m.

Bit of a send for an hour on the lanes. Legs were munching it up nicely today so just went with it.
Spin pre last exam. Looked a bit dreary and cold outside so just sat on the turbo.
Exams finito, free man for the summer. Went and practised some rollerski afterwards, was fun.

30mins easy -> 10*1min[1min] -> 10mins easy.

A late job after a day planting up some inheritance with the father. Giro once again making this much easier, very sweaty afterwards and some very suspect smells.

49.88 km (24.4 kph) +795m.

Spin in the rain.

35.84 km (23.5 kph) +704m.

Seat6, first 3 with Peds then solo. Nice morning out there. Up in Edi to see the physio, see what's what avec the foot.
Physio reckons bruised bone, no stressy. She recommended just building back into running straight away and the bruising should go in a couple weeks time, happy days.
Turbo time. Set up with a nice view of the meadows, ideal.
Just did the core part after turbo.

40.79 km (26.2 kph) +779m.

2 laps easy, 3 laps taking the climb and the flat section hard, then 2 laps easy. Felt alright on the efforts. It was such nice weather, could have kept going for ages but needed a pee real bad and also brekky was too tempting. Will run this afternoon :)

Back in the game. Legs had zero clue what was going on, I had to concentrate so hard at the start just to run and not fall over, also both myself and my watch had no idea what sort of pace I was running, somewhere in the 4-6min/km is my best estimate. Foot real good tho, will roll from here :)

48.02 km (26.6 kph) +511m.

Morning Gladhouse with Fiona. Lovely weather so a very enjoyable one.

Whythop woods. Down very briefly to collect my stuff and to also collect some Pfizer antibodies, can't wait to be tracked by the government ;)
Anyways the run was pretty good, very much a raz, however aerobically felt v comfy, quads a bit mashed from the cycling so downhills were shuffled, but then moving well on the Bass track. Happy days, time to get jabbed.

34.48 km (24.9 kph) +476m.

3 Seat and Dudingston laps, this route was rather good, will be repeating.
Morning turbo action. Left arm really quite sore from the jab but apart from that no side effects :)
Back at it.

Up in Fort William aiding Ali and Timbos Ramsay round. Had about 3 hours sleep curled up on the back seat of the car before this so not great feels but actually woke up nicely by the end. Lovely little run on path/trod in Glen Nevis.

31.71 km (27.9 kph) +362m.

Lap of Loch Leven after dropping Bash off at his car, headwind for the first half but then a sweet second half back into Kinlochleven. Such nice roads.

FVO event @ Coilhallan North.

Back at it!! Had a few foot ouchies when I stood on things on the bit it's bruised, but only a few times and the vast majority was good. Technically was a bit rusty, overshooting the final orange standard control was a personal highlight, and also the terrain speed was not there in the slightest, just couldn't run through any of the crap at any sort of speed, however I'm confident these things will come back pretty quickly! Took the dub so that's all that matters right  ;)

27.66 km (25.9 kph) +263m.

Scoot about some cycle paths post car drop off.

40.0 km (24.9 kph) +578m.

Seat and Dudingston laps. Busting for a pee pee the whole way.
Turbo tings.

10' Tempo + 6*800m [75s]

Bloody disaster trying to get onto the track at Saughton, so we just bailed onto the tarmac loop round the park. The 800s were just one lap reps, so approx 800m. The old forerunner 10 was giving me some naughty paces haha, guys watches said ~3.20mins/km for the tempo and then 2.27, 27, 27, 27, 25, 26 mins for the laps. Just tucked in behind Craig Morris for the whole thing, tempo felt very good actually, could chat the whole way, aerobic system is good, legs just need to get there.

29.85 km (25.6 kph) +434m.

Seat 3, Dudingston 2. Pretty nice actually, legs had some massive insta doms from the session which was less nice.

61.88 km (25.0 kph) +423m.

Nice morning spin with AJ and Matt. Bit bloody soggy but company made it enjoyable. Quite a lot of new roads for me which is always fun.

FVO event @ Calander Park.

Shat myself when I stood on a bit of metal sticking out the ground and it went through the shoe, luckily no damage to the foot but was a close call. Good practise holding the line through some rough stuff, summer vegetation is pretty much here :(

19.86 km (24.3 kph) +329m.

Seat3, no way was I making the 7am pedley ride after yesterday's excursions so a solo job this morn. Quite nice and warm, and legs started to feel good on the 3rd lap which was nice. Bike is not in a good state atm, might just ride it into the ground.

Polmaise O-ints.

With gg and spongey. Bit of a shock running at speed in terrain again and the nav was struggling because of it. Felt much better moving in the terrain than Sunday though so that's a big plus, just need to get the nav used to it again.
Lunch date with peds. Summer vibes on the meadows was class.

Sprint Scotland 1 - Crieff- 8th.

Running fast still not feeling very good but hey ho. Cleanish race and beat nobs which is all I can ask for.

Sprint Scotland 2 - Bannockburn - 8th.

Legs pretty mashed at this point so didn't enjoy the running nature of the course but gurned my way round without too much faff. A couple of sub optimal routes but no mistakes as such.

Aughingarrich 2nd +4mins on gg.

Legs abso gone, just had no terrain give at any point really. Contemplated dropping out but nah that ain't for me, ground it out and actually very happy to keep the nav on point apart from one 30s job. Feels like I've just finished a training camp or something, so hopefully with a bit of rest this coming week the legs start going again. Quality area tho and a good course so I did kinda enjoy it ;)
Core and dat. A successful day of fug all completed.
Morgonplod with peds. Warm already :))
Pootle to get le car.
Pedley dragged me from my slumber for a double meadows lap morning. Pretty nice.

4 * ~10mins @ Newton Fell.

LOC event, didn't just wanna yeet round the full thing so broke it up into segments of 4 controls. Proper weird area, some fairly normal open fell then into some mad bushy shiz which I just couldn't deal with. Anyways legs feeling OK, I think another 2 easy days will sort em out.
Bba up the hill behind the house, stop for the views and then home. Waaaarm already. Forgot how much harder running is in the heat, Sunday could be pretty grim in that respect...!

WCOC event @ Fellbarrow.

Nice course planned by big Herbie. Leggies feeling actually pretty good, exciting times.
Lovely good vibes joggo. Massive amounts of pollen atm.
4 * 15s. Post drills.

BOC Middles - 4th.

Knew I was gonna be on the ropes physically but also knew just needed the get the nav right. Legs actually feeling good and I was moving okay, a few too many small mistakes and two larger 45s ones. Not good enough to fight at the top today, onto tomorrow's big job, let's fooking get after it.

Northern Champs - 3rd.

Big old grind. Right foot has pretty bad plantar fascitis atm and the bruised bone on left foot was a bit aggravated from yesterday so I was swearing a fair amount at those. Nav was good for the majority, went through a bad patch technically at 5,6,7 and then the legs were complaining a lot up to 8. Felt like I was just cruising for a wee while after that, but nav was good. Started to push on again to 17 and held an okay pace to the finish, two gels doing bits in stopping the bonk. All in all never felt like I could race it but I was strong and had mostly good nav, so still up there in results. Annoyingly close to woc spots both days but 3 week ago I couldn't run so I can't complain too much. Looking forward to summer skog :)

59.55 km (25.6 kph) +460m.

Ride out into East Lothian with AJ. Quality weather and nice roads made for an excellent morning out. Had a rather comedic moment when AJ stopped rather quickly in-front of me and I piled into the back of him which resulted in me upside down in the hedge.
Crags with Leitchpu and Callum. Stopped at the top to watch some firemen exciting times.
Pfh including the scree run. Lovely stuff indeed.

12.84 km (22.3 kph) +238m.

Puncture time. WOC middle here we come!!!
Seat scrambles with David. Lovely stuff.
Easy meadows, legs feeling okay so faster than usual.
Ben Lomond loop. Leggies feeling fairly back to normal now so enjoyed this a lot. Cloudy at the top but nice views lower down and finished with a swim, ideal.
Morning pootle with Mosson. Good stuff, will attempt a session this afternoon :0

2km + 10*400m @ Holyrood High grass track.

2km at tempo, then a lap jog, then the 400s starting every 2 mins. 2km in 6.42ish then ~72s for the 400s. The 2km felt okay, but leggies not happy going faster on the 400s, just not used to it and quads tight from the hillage yesterday. It's a start at least, and good news is there's much room for improvement in the coming 3 weeks!
Dundurn Otek. Niiiice one.

Scottish Champs

Still having some slight foot problems so not quite commiting through the terrain as I'd like, but ran fairly strongly the whole way, legs feeling very bang average. 7 was in the wrong place so I lost 4-5mins there, thought of Felix beating me got me shifting for the rest tho :0 Fortunately he's all talk and no walk ;)
Core. Spent the afternoon gardening for the grandparents, quite fun actually :)
Colouring in the meadows on a lovely morning.
4 strides.

10 * 1min [jog down] hills.

With Sunley and Spendog up above Buttermere. Working well and followed up with a swim in the lake so an excellent afternoon all round.
*down in the Lakes to get the second vaccine.
Pre running the Father's event up on Angle Tarn. Really cool up in the clouds, very little visibility and there was also little canes out so a high quality training all in all.
Jog in the Whythop woods. Lovely stuff, crashed pretty hard this afternoon, not feeling very prime after the vaccine yesterday. Feeling fine now tho so we roll on.

Grass threshy - 4*5mins [1min].

3.28, 28, 22, 28. On the rugby pitches. Legs feeling quite okay, just kept it chill, bloody warm already!
4 strides

WCOC event @ Knock Murton

Took it out fairly hard chasing down spenny, he missed to 9 so I got ahead. After this I just did enough to stay ahead, no need to properly bury myself! Very good fun indeed.
Hermitage and a quarry scramble. Leggies feeling kinda tired, but some lovely weather so all good in da hood.
Core etc pre run.
Docharn and Dieschar.

Seat lap. Had planned on running a middle at Culbin this morning but I woke up bonked af, head was spinning, feeling a bit sick and couldn't really see so I gave that a pass and napped instead. Think just everything catching up with me, odd coz I felt fine this afternoon, as always sleep cures all. Also I'm still yet to run in Culbin, will get there one day.
BBM early doors. Flying to Czech today, hopefully!

Big old sweaty travel day yesterday so taking it chill today ft waiting for a PCR test result (negative whoop). It's a bit warm here, but cannot wait to get into the skog tomorrow :) Also Ralph come feed me I'm hungry ;)

10 * 2mins[1min] on trail.

Felt like some good work banked, pushed fairly hard on the last few but felt comfy for the rest. Was about 18°C and raining today which I'd take every time over the 30°C of the last couple days. Middle this afternoon :)
Up to the start ft running straight through the firing range Ralph told me to avoid.
Bramberk middle - Map Gooooood fun :) did contemplate wearing my England o-top ahead of tonight but the number of chainsaw wielding locals I met probably good I didn't.
private note:
I need to maintain good height awareness on slopes. Do this by following the contours and by having some good big features to tick off on the slope, i.e. obvious rocks/veg.

Keep that compass hooooot, I need to be running as straight as I can.

description: Malinik Middle - Map Running a Swedish team training, they did it as a middle qualifier I believe. Most of them ran in the low 30s (I assume at a good efffort) which doesn't seem too far away if pushed. Technically pretty good, one wobble to 6 but apart from that nice and smooth. Nice forest.
private note:
To get through the rough patches know the entry direction then just push through it hard.

Just keep being one feature ahead, boulder, veg etc etc.

description: Jog up the big hill behind the house. Was misty at the top so no nice views :( Still very cool.
Morning jog with Ralph. Good stuff.
Grim forest and my right plantar flared up pretty bad. Need some rest.
Malinik Middle. Foot straped up, actually very little pain, just ache so the rest has done good. Tough forest but tekkers okay.
Jog at Slovanka. Foot feeling fine.

Middle Selection race at Tanvald.

Took it hard up to 11, had intended running the full thing hard but legs were feeling pretty tired about 20mins in, so pulled the plug early and jogged real easy round the rest. Plantar all good which was very nice. Will just run once a day and hope for some nicer legs next tuesday.

Middle course on the model area courtesy of Thierry so there was a start list, si, etc etc. Area was mega mega tough, hoping the race areas are a bit easier but probably best to prepare like its like this!
Morning jog with Mr Robertson round a lake. Good Times and foot felt fine, may even do some hill strides tonight.
Some cool sandstone trails with PeteB from the accom post pcr test, accreditation etc etc. Fun fun times :)

Trail session with the room-mate. 10' tempo + 4*30s hills. I just followed him on the tempo and we didn't go slow for the conditions, felt good. Lower right leg got a mashing from the physio this, will hopefully help the foot but it was rather sore!
Micro O from the accom.
Jog in the forest near the hotel. So nice in terrain the whole way. Sprint viewing this afternoon! Exciting.
Core and dat.

2 courses on the model map taken at race pace. Moving okay through the real rough stuff and nav similarly okay, just need to avoid the mistakes on the race and choose lines through nicer running parts and will be grand.
Jog with PeteB.

WOC middle Quali - 16th.

F
Long/ Relay model. This sandstone stuff is infinitely nicer than the mountain shiz I've been playing in the last couple weeks.
Some sandstone across the road from the accom. Fun stuff.
Garmin shat it about half way through. Lap of the lake, saw the Germans then the French ladies oo la la.
Core et all.
Travel day sneaking my way into Finland :0
Tour de Helsinki central Park with Olli. On the small trails at a very easy pace, muchos enjoyment.

Fin5 day 2 open class.

Bloody excellent stuff.

20 * 1min [30s]

Relaxed intro back to the grind.

Fin5 day 3 open class.

More good skog at an easy speed.
Jog on the trails.
Travel to Jukola camp, very nice. Foot still not too happy so limiting the training atm, probably 8hrs running this week and will see what happens.

Jukola Camp #1

Easy O @ Sarrioselkä. Very nice forest, actually very straightforward, just poon a bearing and pick up the big shapes and the odd boulder, enjoyed muchos. Did 4*15s strides afterwards as well, nearly ran into Rudolf on one of them!
private note:
Straight is best always, so to orienteer.

Take the time to get the exit right. Keep the compass live.
Tick off the contour shapes.
Use boulders and distinct veg.

description:
Jukola Camp #2

Course at a good speed focusing on going as straight as possible. Was going okay until I hit the nasty area with lots of branches and rocks then I really struggled.
private note:
Straight is good but not king. King is running very fast straightish looking for good lines.

Once in the circle really keep your head up and scan for the control.

Push through the rough patches and sacrifice map reading for speed here because you can't read the map. Alternatively look for the nice round routes. Routes are sorted at/ before the control.

description:
Jukola Camp #3.

Slope-O. Had quite a lot of small mistakes this morning. Probably need to run a bit faster to make everything work properly. It was also pissing it down for a change.
private note:
Check direction, especially just before about to commit through a tough section, I.e. downhill, through rough stuff etc.

Do your own thing, don't get distracted by other controls and other people.

description:
Jukola Camp #4

4 Oints with Einar and Veli, starting 40s apart in different orders each time. I ran very well, with maybe 30s of mistakes total. Fitness coming back slowly so the speed wasn't outstanding but yes quite pleased for now :)

On another note my foot is feeling the best it has for a couple months so hopefully can keep it going in the right direction!

Jukola Camp #5

Real easy through some green stuff at Hiidenkirnut. I took many path routes to maintain the British reputation. Managed to smack my foot off a branch and fall over multiple times, slow orienteering really isn't the one.

Jukola Camp #6

Middle race. I felt okay but am at the stage of the camp where no matter how hard I push the legs won't go too fast. Anyways technically okay but I got spanked the Finns, Topi ran 32ish which is pretty mentally fast. Also I somehow managed to twist my ankle this morning without noticing and it swelling up in the afternoon, but swelled ontop of my foot which is weird af, anyways taped it and was fine.
private note:
I need to read less details, especially on longer legs, just fucking send it hard and straight.

Ne really strict around the control, get the route abandoned get the compass going and then move faaaast!!

description: Long old drive from Rovaniemi down to Helsinki, good opportunity to take a rest.
Miles with eikka, round some bay. Was some pretty nice views and legs felt good. Had a poop halfway and felt much better afterwards.
Core on some grass somewhere.

Gravel ints with Einar, Eikka, Luke in some park near Lukes house. I did 6*lap, times were 5.08, 4.56, 4.55, 4.52, 4.46, 4.42.
Very nice progression feeling comfy until the last rep which felt quite hard. Lap had a few hills and twists and turns so was good fun and paces pretty good as well. Went for a swim after was ideal.
Jog w/ eikka. ran out of clean running clothes now so ran in swim shorts, was a short enough run to avoid the chaffing.
Small trails in the woods with Eikka and Luke.

O-ints with the guys in Nuuksio. 5 intervals, I fugged the first one then good 2nd one, okay 3rd and 4th ones and a very good last one. Basically I can do it very well when I decide to and run at the front, I'm a bit useless at following tho.
private note:
I need to be in the correct mental state for these hard training  I am going in to hurt myself and have the technique on point.
I should just run my own orienteering and use the others for speed, not just sit in.

#1 I just needed slightly better picture of the circle
#2 again just do your own thing
#3 based

2nd loop. I ran my own thing and ran very well.

#9 plough straight, you can back off the speed and take slightly better lines. Know when to use the aggression push.
#10 aggressive mud leg, then slow down into tricky circles.

Consider routes on every control.

description: Ride alongside Eikka on his evening miles.
More small trails in the skog. First run this long in a good while so had some excellent fun and no bonking which was ideal.
private note: little toe left foot, left foot bottom and left hip all sore :(

description: Orienteering at Lohja. I was planning on razzing round a long course but bailed quite early as it was stupidly hot and the terrain wasn't particularly nice and I also bonked, not ideal, not very happy with myself.
Afternoon miles with eikka, finished at the sea for a swim.
Back to the flat.
Core
Jog with the guys.
Gravel Thresh with eikka and einar. 6 loops of a park with 2mins in between. Felt okie dokie.
Dub dub.
Small trails, up to Kuopio this weekend for some racing :)
Jig and then a bit of orienteering but foot was too sore

ViestiLiga

Was doing well, about 1min behind the leader in the big pack but then I twisted my ankle and had to walk the rest. Very very frustrating.

Rest day vibes. I've decided that I've had enough of being injured so for the foreseeable future I will only try and run 7-8hrs a week and then a but load of XT on the top of that, as well as core and maintenance on alternating days. I am sick of being mediocre, it is time to stop fucking about and time to start chasing the dreams properly.

28.95 km (23.0 kph) +244m.

Some gravel trails and some pavements in eastern Helsinki. Letting the ankle settle, I could run on road today if I needed to but I don't so there. Might go bosh a few segments this afternoon :)

28.34 km (26.9 kph) +245m.

Razzing about on the gravel paths and went for a seggy effort but came up 4s short. Sure I'll be back at some point to get it.
Maintenance stuff.

Run in idre fjäll. Such a nice place and the run ended on a hill with a very atmospheric sunset looking onto the Norwegian mountains. Also many rudolfs wandering about, some rather large with some rather large antlers!

Big day of travel setting off at 5.45 finnish time and arriving here at 18.55 swedish Time, but got plenty of naps in so not feeling very tired. Just just got here in time before the supermarket shut which was a big big win as would have had to wait till 9am tomorrow for my next meal otherwise :/ Wanted to do an hour of XT this morning at Arlanda whilst waiting for my train and I'd read you could go to one of the hotel gyms but the guy at reception was having none of it ffs, what a tool bag. Hope to use the gym here or get my hands on  a mountain bike somehow.

On the injury front my left ankle was good for the majority, still sore with any sudden inward movements, right foot completely fine but I'm sure that willstart hurting again soon enough. Right hip got really quite tight as well near the end which was odd. Hey ho, I'd say that was one of the least painful runs of the past few months tbh!

I had planned on doing o-ints but about 30s in I realised the ankle wasn't ready for it so I bailed and did 4*5mins hill reps. Moving okay I think just once again frustrated too not do the planned training for about the 100th time his summer. Everything felt good tho on the tracks, apart from the hips which got real tight on the down hills.

Jogging a lap of Gränjåsvålen (the mountain behind Idrefjäll). Started out on a big gravel track, then small single-track which then turned into (very nice) terrain. I boshed this for a while, ankle holding up rather fine, just sore now and then until I hit another big track and was just on these till the end. Saw a dude in an SNO top and he biked alongside me for a while arking about the world cup and Ralph, fun times. Should have brought the rollerskis cos there's loads of people doing it and many tracks for it, unbelievable stuff.

Skog. Ankle not quite there yet so I couldn't really nav very well whilst focusing on it so I bailed. Maybe I'll finish this course by the end of my stay, but probably not. I do realise my training is shite atm but I'm doing the best I can.
Wee tempo on the trails whilst planning the rest of the course.

Städjan the local big hill. Actually quite rocky and tekky trails for the most part, ankle holding up okay, just a bit sore now and then. Very nice scenery and saw many reindeer. Did take longer than expected tho but legs feeling okay.

On the model map. Spanked the tekky controls and bottom section but my compass was shit in the vague bit. Found it so hard to run with the rocks and my ankle, I hope that on Thursday it is less sore but today was still not too fun with it. Either way should be some good racing coming up
Jogging after moving up to the team accom. Got bloody soaked in a monsoon and hail, was gonna run an hour but was getting cold so bailed home and will do the rest later.
Joggo with Josh on some trails. Very nice, leggies feeling good. Did two strides at the end and legs felt grand. Just hope ankle holds up tomorrow for 17km of skog, big yikes.

Probably my worst performace ever. Ankle was sore with every step so I couldn't push physically and also was focusing on that not the nav so made plenty of mistakes. SO FUCKING FRUSTRATING! I'll be back for sure, although need to have a good long think about how to deal with the ankles going forward.
Jog on big trails. I'm not racing the other events or doing jukola, coming home on Monday. I can't race with that much pain.

private note:
Summer 2021 learning.

- I can't race whilst sore and injured.
- I want to be at the race place 3 days before. 2 day before do ~15mins of otervals on the model. Day before Jog and strides.
- I need to spend more time in terrain so I can move better in it.
- ankles: I will buy a brace/ VJ high tops to train in. Race heavily taped up
- ankles: I will do Bosu work every day
- In terms of training don't do too much running, want to feel comfy, no stressy niggles. Run once a day and XT once a day and S&C once a day. Take a rest day once a week.
- I need at least two camps in relevant terrain, only do this for the big races of the year, EOC/WOC. First one is a week of normal camp, second one should be some races.
- I need to prepare better technically, more geeking and stuff.
- In the race I need a better more consistently aggressive mindset, just go into beast mode for the full thing.

description: Out and back run on big trails and roads.
Lovely little trail run.
Back in the Burgh. Time to get fit.

8 * 3mins [90s] on the meadows.

I have got some bunda to lose but this was okay. Next 7 weeks I hope to a) get stronger ankles and wear braces so I don't twist them again b) lose some bunda c) Do lots of running and cycling and enough orienteering to hopefully have some good races this year at Euromeeting and the autumn races.
Should have done more on this.

25.26 km (20.8 kph) +438m.

Seat4 with Felix, I was on his town bike which was a bit large for me and also quite a whopper. Still had fun and impressed to see Felix do a seat climb no handed.
Shortenhall on a lovely morning. Hopefully I am acquiring a gravel bike this afternoon :0

20.8 km (20.6 kph) +250m.

Pootle on Felixs bike. I acquired a gravel/Cross bike this afternoon, it needs a bit of tlc but should be good to roll soon, am very excited.

Was on my way to raz some seat climbs, bumped into Mr Laraia who was gonna do a session so we combined and did 4*purkos from the Loch. I kept it fairly chill which was nice, legs feeling quite okay for the majority.

20.52 km (20.4 kph) +243m.

Evening gravel, still on Felixs bike, soon onto mine.
Core and balance. Actually 30mins of work.
Bit of mostly tarmac pounding up the canal, along greenbank drive, down hermitage and then back via the meadows. Actually really nice route, legs moving fine but quads defo a bit tired.

21.85 km (20.6 kph) +330m.

New bike whoop whoop, good fun cutting about on the grass and did an APO job as well.

Bosh into the Pentlands with Felix. Jogged up the valley then smashed up Carnethy the steepest way, 1.18km with 331m of climb in 12:16. Reckon can go sub 11 at some point, especially with fresher legs. Maybe something for the winter. Back along the ridge via Turnhouse afterwards.

27.56 km (24.1 kph) +296m.

Out making bare dollar in a Facebook marketplace sell. Got rained on.
Core which felt easy today for some reason.
Skyline with FW, AliM, Bashman, Oleg, Jill and Totton. Highly enjoyable especially as I didn't bonk this time :)
Big old rest day. At home in the Lakes for this week.

15 * 90s[45s] on the Thirlemere Road.

Kept everything pretty chill, just ticking them off. A lovely day and always a good place to session with good views. Enjoyed it.

25.36 km (17.7 kph) +507m.

Road and trail mix. Setmurthy, then round the back of Sale Fell and through Whythop woods. Slow times on some of the trails, need to get my tekkers up.

28.1 km (21.0 kph) +522m.

Getting this gravel bike had opened up a whole new realm of climbs to explore, today I went up the track towards Dodd which was a mega grind. Good fun tho.
Pootling about on Sale Fell with the working man (spender) warm out!
Core pre ride.

23.95 km (21.8 kph) +384m.

Controversial morning cycle, hopefully orienteering tonight :0

WCOC Event @ Ling Fell.

A nice reminder of why I go abroad to orienteer in the summer  muchos bracken and thistles kicking about. Ankle survived butI was being super cautious on anything rough.
Whinlatter Joggo. Saw some llamas.
Core et al

27.1 km (22.4 kph) +448m.

Poole on the lanes. Tried a new road but big private signs and couldn't be sacked with an altercation with a farmer so turned around.
Into the fells. Pub afterwards with the father. Good stuff.
Got to the event quite late so a very rushed warm up, pee and poop, then onto the race.

Tentsmuir event.

First fast orienteering in a long time with no pain from any bodily parts so I was very happy. Used new ankle brace which worked well. Terrain speed pretty bad, overall fitness okay but just couldn't push into the hurt locker. However it was awesome to be orienteering fast again and I've never been in Tentsmuir and was pleasantly surprised:)

25.47 km (24.7 kph) +190m.

Bit of main road boshing on Cornettos bike from Templars bike. Headwind the whole way back.
Body logged out on me last night, was sweating and shivering all night and have spent the day in bed.
Poole about Templars. Feeling normal apart from my stomach which is in a mess as I've been lying down for about 40 hours, sure it'll clear soon.
Ooft, not a chance back to Monday vibes and in bed all day.

An interesting night trying to sleep amidst a euoc piss up. Once asleep I kept waking up every couple hours completely soaked with sweat, got the towel out, dried off, back to sleep and repeat. However the more I sweated the better I was feeling and some quite normal feels this morning, happy days.
Jog round some muir of dinnet O. Bloody feeling okay, ankle fine. Stomach inte bra.

SOL @ Balmedie.

Was supposed to be doing SHIs this weekend but had to bail on that for some obvious reasons. Easy round actually really enjoying myself, had Leitchpu up ahead most the course which was entertaining. Ankle fine on the dunes. Stomach not feeling good. Rest of body feeling okay but still a bit shivery. New goal for the next few weeks is to stop feeling like shit.
Part of the Black at the SOL. Body feeling basically normal, ankle okay. Orienteering not so good, oh well, feels like a long time I've been worried about the nav rather than injuries.

21.55 km (21.2 kph) +319m.

Lots of fun cutting about some trails and grass, felt pretty good as well. Only issue with the body now is the stomach.

6 * 3mins [2mins] on meadows.

Kinda okay but one of the days where I was struggling every rep in the second half. A good re-introduction to hard running after my bonk. Feel like I'm at the stage where if I do this session again next week it'll be faster and feel better, something to look forward to. Did a long cool down and was running on only a banana this morning so some good tired feels at the end.
PFH prebrekky with peds, fw and bash. Good fun but had dead legs the whole way.

10.04 km (18.8 kph) +53m.

Nice mess about on KF. Just to get outside really and to get the legs moving again.

Sprintervals @ Liberton

5 courses of varying length with Thompass. 1, 3, 5 mass start and 2 and 4 chasing. Running very much at threshold as legs a bit tired, couldn't ever push into the red. Anyways I really enjoyed it and tekkers were okay.

19.26 km (17.3 kph) +405m.

A little Pentlands foray. Up the big army track to nearly Castlelaw and back.

2 * "Carnethy from the Bridge" with a not slow descent in between. Running with Spendog for the whole thing just finding a nice rhythm and not squeezing the bottle too much. JoeW "won" the first rep then didn't do a second, classic moves there ;)
Lil double big meadows lap double. Legs felt good :)
Big shuffle jog with Peds for most and Spender for all. Late night so some bonky bonky feels.

41.38 km (19.3 kph) +661m.

7 hills with Davros. Excellent fun cutting about Edi.
Morning meadows with peds. Slow start but got into it nicely. Drills then strides to finish.

Livingston sprintervals.

With PeterM, Grace, Shminty, Spongey and Fiona. 6 intervals. Very good fun and ran quite okay for the majority.
Morning pootle round Hermitage. Legs feeling quite empty, didn't manage to eat much after training yesterday as the stomach was not in a good mood.
Slap.
Core
Cheap WoL miles.
Over to help at euoc taster session.
Back from helping at euoc taster session.
Core and dat. Might cycle, but equally I'll be out and about helping with the hill race so no harm in an easier day with the VK tomorrow :0

Mamores VK.

Ran a bit shit but looks like the dub and £200 is in the bank so swings and roundabouts eh.
Maze-O. Got ruined by Felix.
Big pootle with Felix.
Gym stuff. Not much tbh, hopefully there is some core next time.
Cross trainer. Sweaty work.

10 * 1min [1min].

Just stretching the legs a bit on the meadows. Keppt the min easy sub 5s just to keep it moving along. Calves very tight from the capacity calf raises yesterday but apart from that all good.
Down to KF, back via bog and lap of meadows to finish. Wore a thermal which was a big mistake.
Nighttime seat action testing out my headtorch. It worked well and the legs felt good. Didn't wear a thermal this time and probably should have.
BnB with Spendog. Feeling quite okay and good chats. Lovely stuff.
4*15s strides.
Italia joggo out to some cool fortress village on lake Garda. 25°C taps aff. Did manage to get a parked fine tho lol

Big old travel day, with the highlight being experiencing Milan rush hour; carnage. Anyways this means I gave the night race a miss and went for a jog on the trails round Riederalp (2000m asl) with a bit more effort on the climbs to get shiz going.
Shake n bake with peds. Some unreal views over to the Matterhorn.

Euromeeting Middle

Yea so gooooood to be back racing (first since WOC, madness) Fitness is pretty ropey after the summer of injury + overtraining a few weeks ago (my bad) but ankle held up well today as did my plantar so I could actually focus on the orienteering which was excellent news. Ran really quite okay for the majority, maybe holding back a bit too much on the downhills but technically good, baring one big 1.40min whopper. This was frustrating but it's nice to be frustrated by a mistake rather than not actually being able to run. So yea onwards and upwards :)

Was sitting in 44th before the mistake which would have been A okay, and lost ~1min on the long leg routechoice so much improvements to be had tomorrow :)

Euromeeting Long

Cloud rolled in very fast just before my start so vis was down to like 5m for the majority of my race. This lead to some stoopid mistakes and then I chose a mega btec route on the long leg. Big yikes.
Jog once at Italy accom. Exploring some trails and crossing a river. Fun.
Long model. Stupidly nice terrain, if the long is like this then I am well up for the 20.km we have.
Jog pre dinny. Legs moving okay but still some soreness kicking about.
Middle model. Had heard about the nettles before so I stuck some plastic bags down me trousers which worked a treat. Terrain was much much rougher.
Afternoon leg stretch with Peds through some vin yards. Feeling gooood.

private note:
Long game plan.

Evaluate every routechoice before the leg.
Compass strong, big shapes fall into place.
45mins, 75mins, 105mins gels.
Start strong, stay strong, full poon.

I will have a clean run with no bonk. Full focus on the orienteering. Route, compass, features.

description: Jog on the WU map.

WC3 Long - 65th.

Did what I set out to do so I'm really quite happy with that. No bonk and running was fine the whole way. Slow to 1 which cost me a bit and two other ~30s slips but apart from that all good. Made sure to check all the routechoices today after my shocker at Euromeeting and most were good. Some dirty field running through spectator and into the finish was not appreciated but was running with Mr Vuitton by this point which made it bearable. Aiming to get my first world cup points (top 40!) in the middle race.
Jog round Lago di Lago and Lago di Santa Maria. Followed by a swim and an ice cream. Getting dropped by the girls; unbelievable.
Shaking it out avec Grace. Legs feeling okay.

WC Middle - 73rd.

Very meh. Excellent terrain and course though.
Joggo with Grace. Legs felt fine but I'm very tiredy atm.
private note:
MSR game plan.

-get my route for each control sorted.
- sit on the back of anyone and grind to stay in them

description:
WC MSR.

Yea not brilliant from myself.
Jog with Fiona and Grace up some rando hill on the way to the airport. Hanging after last night but tbh got away with it quite lightly.
Back to cold rainy Edi, back to work.
Turbo time. Watching cycling videos, muchos enjoyment.
Lunchtime wander round the city. Checking out Calton Hill to make sure there's no major issues for fwtn tomorrow, lap of the seat and then some meadows. Lovely and sunny, felt okay, enjoyed it.

Pre n post gym with pedley. We started incredibly slow as per but an hour of activation later and peds started running somewhat fast :0 ;) Also got an apple from Dudingston and then I had to listen to pedley violently nose breathing as he ate it up going up a hill. What a morning.
Some good work. Will be squatting 100kg by December ;)
Fwtn business.
Bit if this bit of that. First half with Dan. Got moving a bit on some climbs which was fun.
Canal and Wol out to see the grandparents. They were doing well and I got exceedingly wet. Legs feeling primed for Skyline tomorrow, let's get after it!

private note:
Skyline plan:

Get to Drove road feeling good, start ramping then rearlly grind for Harbour onwards.

Eat at 40mins, 80mins, 120mins. Bar, gel, gel. Drink at these times as well and whenever you get a chance take water.

I want to run sub 2.40.

description:
Pentlands Skyline - 3rd.

Great fun until about Bells Hill, then I started bonking badly. Just ploughed on and held the position, wanted a sub 2.40 and was nearly at a sub 2.30 so I'm quite a happy and massively ruined potato right now.

private note:
Skyline review:

I think I started quite hard but really that was the right pace and I just needed more leg strength.

The bars didn't work well, I should have just used gels. Also I need to be careful when opening the gels so I can actually eat it.

Maybe could have gone deeper on the final few climbs but I buried myself well today. More fight on the last descent would have been good.

description:
16.07 km (16.0 kph) +94m.

To gym and then mooching around KF. Good fun, nice evening.
"Gym". Did mobility and balance and lots of complaining about the legs, ideal.
Massive plod with Spenny. Legs not good at all.
Hermitage with Pedley.
Seat lap. Hangover has hit and I needed a poop. Fun.
Pfh. Legs feeling a bit tiredy but pretty normal. Windy out, but nice and dry. Good times
Hermitage loop and then a few meadows laps. Lovely stuff in the sun. Legs feeling A-okay, just in time to mash them at FRAs and CSC this weekend :))

FRAs Leg 2 w Peds.

Legs felt pretty horrible for the majority, Skyline still kicking about for sure. We nailed the routechoices though which made for an exciting finale. Unfortunately the ankle was feeling rather weak so didn't want to fully poon it off the final hill. Big up Felix and Bisset as well, unbelievable stuff from them :0

private note:
CSC Final preview.

This is going to be very good practise for those final few races when the legs are dead but you have to perform. I want to win. Technically I want to race hard on the paths and take aggressive lines corner cutting. Then I need a bit of control coming in and off paths. I also don't want to twist the ankle so I will tape it well.

description: Stakeout w peds.

CSC Final.

Ah won't actually write much, basically my ankle went yesterday so was mincing hard in the terrain and legs stuck in 3rd gear after yesterday. Ankle got really bad mid way so couldn't focus and then made some fairly hefty mistakes. Another frustrating one to end 2021, basically the more I've tried this year the worse I've got, need to rest and reset for next year now.
