Ploddo up the crags with a stop to chat with Thompass (juicy goss, oi oi @FW) and then Gregor later on.
Two weeks of this then will build back up to 2022!
Meadows.
Before gym with Dan, then home with peds.
Gym
Another 30mins, very exciting.
Meadows again. With Dan and Noah and we ran through an Anti-vax rally, lolol. Wonder when the sub 5s will come into play again haha.
Seat with spenny, including spuds crack.

15.86 km (21.1 kph) +231m.

Ppre gym KF lap and then 2 seat laps. All good fun until the crank started falling off, luckily it remained in place till the gym.
Gym. 3*5 squats at 70, 80, 80. Working up to the big hundo;)
Hermitage and Blackford scramble with Dan. Got nipped by a dog, wee bastard. Apart from that very enjoyable.
Seat. Didn't quite make euoc long run as was solving some mafs. Anyways good fun scrambling about, bit sketchy on the slippy rocks but we survived. Best I've felt in a good few weeks :)
Hermitage loop with Dan. Wet but some goood chats so was goood fun. Feeling surprisingly okay...
Slap plod. Got quite dark.
Strides. Nearly time to play the training game again.
Finishing off FWs big job with him. He was shifting so well, respect.
Pentlands bosh with pedley, fiona and bashman. Pretty terrible weather but some good levels of chat were maintained so time flew by. Did the scree and a new path at the end, excellent stuff.
To/from gym.
Lots of chat, not much action. "Easy" week.
Cross trainer. First bit with wozzle and pippa, noice. Got sweaty sweaty sweaty.

Hounds session - 8/2 + 2*4/1 + 8/2.

Thought this was gonna be grim but I just tucked in and rolled with it. Did feel like we were running unbelievably fast to begin with but I got used to it again and soon felt comfy. Started hurting a bit on the last rep so backed off a few meters from AJ and Bobby and finished at my own pace. Was very good fun, look forward to more :)
4*30s. Spud speeeeeed.
Tried to make the euoc run but some misplaced flat keys stopped that plan so was just scooting about some lines solo. Got a handful of bird shit going up the crack, delightful.
Did some decent work and had some good chat. Successful morning.

Cruising round the Morrtonhall fwtn. Got a front row seat to the RickyP mistake show. Tbf my tekkers were a bit sloppy at times as well. Great fun had tho, even tho I finished and had to immediately destroy some bushes...
Collecting with Spongey and JT. Found a football, unreal scenes.
Easy easy crags and crack combo. With Dan and Joe then the Campbells joined for a brief moment as well. Fun times.
Livingston sprinting. Ran course 3 and split it into 3 intervals. Was bloody moist out so was Tokyo drifting a lot of the corners. Overall okay.
private note:
1. Route sorted by the control.
2. Simple plans, key features.
3. Push hard out of every corner

description: NightO ints with GG and peds. Running with gg for the majority, pretty grotty area but good training. An exciting afternoon. Straight back to Edi and suited up!
Pentlands with a big squad. Abso clattered my knee last night so that was really quite sore. Gooood times :)
There and back again.
Good, back on the squats. Tried out the 100kg and didn't die.
Elliptical tings. Did enjoy switching off for a bit.

Hounds but not hounds, hmm. Their session was a bit weird so me, Bobby, Dashwood, Ewan and Todge went with some classic 8s and 4s. 3*8/2 + 4/1 for me. Paces fine, aerobically feeling grand but legs and back were not impressed by the squatting yesterday so had to force them to go a bit. Anyways solid work banked, won't go so hard in gym next week lol.
Inc 4*30s.
Pfh with mosson, fw and peds. Bit of an early start but leggies actually felt good once we were going. Nice light up on the tops, excellent stuff.
To/from gym. Walked out the flat as Alice was jogging past, then fiona joined later and Dan on the way home, excellent stuff.
Decent work.
Cutting about places with Dan and Breeze. Lovely lovely sunshine.
Joggo with a goood amount of peeps. Did some rouge hospital loops as well, love to see it.
4*15s on grass. Just cultivating the sprint finish before tomorrow, let's goooooo.
A singular meadows lap wake up with pedley. Nicee skies.

BOC Relays.

3rd leg. Sent out in 2nd place alone chasing Spongey. Started at a pace I should be able to race at but the lack of fitness atm got me, also ankles not great. Technically okay and nice to be pretty much exactly same time as the FVO team boys. Need to be able to close those gaps down tho if we want to win next year. Onwards.
Pfh. Had some serious talks with myself.
Jim
Elliptical. Forgot the headphones so this was looooong.

Hounds, 8/2 + 2*4/1 + 8/2 + 2*4/1.

Leggies feeling nice this evening so I was leading my little group of Bobby, Dashwood and a new guy called David. Nice to be able to run that feeling comfy, won't happen every week so gotta take it when it comes :)
3 boys, all in need of a toilet.
Slap with pedley. Nice morning, body feeling tired but legs all good.
Cats Nick and then the traverse into climb on the seat. Good fun, first time up the nick, an excellent addition to the seat scramble portfolio.
To/from gym.

FwtN @ Braids.

Good start with Bash, then messed about on a bush at the start of the phi. Twisted the ankle a bit coming out of the phi so was jogging it for a control, then that got better so started going again. Was a bit off Bash and spongey in the later section but taking better lines so closing, then took a bad routechoice near the end so ended up a bit behind. Just needed a bit more composure and would have been in the sprint finish mixer, but happy off tired legs from Tuesday. Rest of the week is pretty chill :))
Collecting.
Ez with Todger and Finn.

Coledale fells. Forgot my thermal so was pretty bloody cold and wet for quite a lot of this, had to keep shifting to keep warm. There is something quite satisfying about pooning about in the clag with not another soul in sight, although should have defo brought more clothes.

Galoppen @ Great Tower.

Didn't want anything too hard so just cruised round at the peak of the tekkers-speed bell curve. Unbelievably nice skog and ankles feeling grand so I was really quite sad when it ended. Blue skies day as well, all round, worth the trip home :)))
Good tings, up to the 90kg squats.
Elliptical. Had headphones this week, much more pleasant.
Early seshwan with Boyan and Noah. Leggies feeling average so didn't push for the 40mins. Managed to knock out 3 limericks mid sesh so an entertaining evening.
Strides.
Seat
Gym stuff.
Seat and a couple meadows lap. Felt alright so kept moving to keep warm. Wisdom tooth is agony atm, need to get myself to a dentist.

Setmurthy in the dark. Went home to the dentist, have some abscess under a filling on top of all the nerves, does explain the constant pain of late. Antibiotics for 7days and some stronger pain killers, woohoo, fun times.

Down to Cockermouth on the North side of the river, so through Blindcrake, Redmain, Woodhall Park. Then back via the Murthy. Cold cold but blue skies and sunshine so all very nice. Fells have some snow on them, might have to go play tomorrow :)

Long one in a winter wonderland blizzard. Out to Sale Fell, then Ling Fell, then home via the Muthy. Bloody slidey on the fells, could have done with some dobs. Had planned a little Skiddaw from home but defo a good shout not to in that weather. About 100m from home I met the aunt who informed me power was out in the village (and is yet to return) so no shower/hot food for me, but it's time like these I have minecraft downloaded on the phone, great entertainment.
Nixons last gym, end of an era, big sad. Anyways we had some fun, including an exercise band + broom catapult system... (Also did do some actual gym, 90kg squats today)
Elliptical, with friends this week, big win.

Raz time on the canal + WoL. Feeling a bit meh at the start, but soon realised was going into a headwind, way back was much better, got moving decently by the end. No seshwan whilst on the antibiotics but lots of good skog upcoming this weekend so not overly worried.

Don't wanna sound like my flatmate but the top of left calf was pretty tight, need to watch it.
Seat with euoc. Did some scrambles then headed down into the park to play on the slides before heading back up and just catching sunset. Bloody excellent stuff.
Gym.
Pootle putting out beginner course.
Joggo round FwtN planned by Davroski. Good stuff. Had a poop stop mid way round. Highlight of the evening was getting a box of hero's from Judy Bell, unbelievable stuff :))

Meadows zigzags joggo. Was hoping to bump into people to run with, met Will but he was just finishing so a solo job sadly. However near the end I met a doggo called spud which will probably be my daily highlight :))

Lakeland Warrior middle - 4th.

A really good slopey area with some cool low vis stuff. Tekkers pretty good, just not tight enough on a few lines and 1 ~20s miss at 18. And I was really pleased that the ankles were grand, however leggies felt completely shite, proper plodding around today. Think we can put that one down to the antibiotics and lack of hard running for a week and a bit.
private note:
Be a bit more realistic, when you have been antibiotics all week don't expect to be racing well physically.

Always exit direction with the compass.

On contoury legs read the height difference.

Compass hot and have some big features to tick off, then know when to pull it back and nav in.

Route - compass + big features - attack.

description:
Lakeland Warrior forest sprint mass start night.

Carnage off the start, then was alone through the first loop of the butterfly, spongey on the back for the second. Then headtorch started to cut out sporadically on the way to the second lot of butterfly loops in the other bit of forest. Got the back up out and pootled round the rest. Absolutely raging. Was in a good battle in the lead with Spongey up to that point, so very gutted to miss out on that.
private note:
I need a reliable head torch.

Don't rush, push hard once you've sorted the nav.

description: Ft some collecting.

Lakeland Warrior Chasing Long.

Legss seizing up whenever I pushed so a pootle round, would have loved to be in the front pack, next time when the bodies in a better state. Enjoyed the good terrain and course instead.
private note:
I need to be better physically over multiple days of tough terrain. I.e. EOC will be 2 days, rest, 2 days.

Start taking wider path lines in the Lakes.

Always always take the time to check long legs routes. ~10s will easily sort the route and is no time in reality.

description: Hounds. Bit sceptical as to how this would go with the way the legs are feeling atm. 3.30s ended up feeling plenty for tonight. Stopped to tie laces after 16min rep so was alone for a bit, but a corner cut got me back with Rim me Rimicans so finished the session with him. Straight into library toilets afterwards...
Pre brekky slap with AJ. Good stuff.
Plod on through the murthy down to Cockermouth. Was very muddy out. Down for some more dentist fun, hopefully the last for a while!
Murthy long run. Razzed the climbs a bit and chill on the rest of it, knew it would be a bit grindy so had the scandi tunes on the go which kept me entertained, #raggarbil.
Plod on the crags pre brekky. Dark dark.
Double meadows lap with Spenny D. Good chats although won't see the boy for a while, cry. Strides at the end.

Qualifier.

GB sprint camp in Leeds. I have very much forgotten my sprint technique so this was interesting, got into it by the end so hopefully the rest of the day is a bit better. Lots of weird barriers and stuff to deal with.

Quarter finals.

Me, Kris, Nathan, Jonny, Shminty and Ben. 2 to get relegated so my chances were not looking too promising starting this one. However in an unbelievable turn of events I pulled out a little 2nd place behind Kris, let's try pull off the same scam again this afternoon haha.
I mean I was just in the pack the first 4 controls then was solo till the finish, doing my own thing and actually orienteering quite well so pleased with that. Would like some more head to head action this afternoon tho.

Semi Final.

Me, Kris, Jonny, Nathan, PaulP and Andrew (Paul and Fay's flatmate). Quite a heavily gaffled one with lots of sneaky inside outside jobs. Got through fairly unscathed into 3rd place behind Kris and Jonny. Some small mistakes though. Once again excellent fun.

Final.

In the end we just went for a mens and woman's final so lots of geezers kicking about. An ungaffled course as well not that we knew that. I started quite hard and tucked into 2nd place in the Shminty train, was running well actually and took some of my own routes but I was a bit wobbly in some of the execution so ended up in 5th in the pack going into the last couple controls. Went full potato mode going to the last control and moved past Shminty, Ben and Jonny (with Kris just a bit too far ahead) Jonny came back at me in the sprint finish and just dipped it on the line.
Can't complain with a 3rd against those guys and Jonny does have a nasty sprint finish on him so yea quite pleased. Maybe need to rethink my plans to not run any sprint races next year...

MSR training.

Pairs team, with running order being WMWM. Sent out in 4th just behind Jonny, Paulp and Kris. Think Kris and Jonny had the same gaffles and I had different, anyways finished maybe 10s behind Kris, 5s behind Jonny. Once again quite surprised I kept up. Second course did not go so well, lots of closed gates confusing things and I didn't cope with it too well. Still good fun.
Some easy sprint tek to end the weekend. Nailed the weekly hourage and didn't get run over so a successful training.
There and back. Legs tired but not sore :)
Drop in gym, took it quite easy after the weekend!
Got all the bangers on, got through it.

40mins tempo on the meadows with Sasha. Had some bowel problems early doors but got that fixed quickly. Leggies still tired from the weekend so only really got moving in the last 10mins of this, ran from ~3.40s -> 3.20s. Felt pretty comfy the whole way which was nice.
Meadows plod. Not much to report.

Duncraggan NightO with gg, spongey and PeterM. Taking it cruisey, legs quite whacked atm so pushing would have probably ended badly. Actually nearly ended badly when my leg went down a big marshy hole and clattered the knee, jogged it off but a bit stiff now. Anyways tekkers okay but feeling a bit clunky in the terrain. Very good fun as per.
To gym the some seat action afterwards. Was bloody boiling!
Only orienteer in today, rip. Had a hockey guy for company then the whole Michael Phelps wannabe squad rolled in, which made it rather busy.
Morningside into Hermitage and home through the hospital. All very pleasant.
Meadows. Met Finn and Swaz which made this much more pleasant.
Some reps of Whinny. Started with chickens coop, then did 3 other from the road back to the top. Legs feeling not so good.
Core etc
Pentlands Pieline.
Joggo round Prestonfield golf course. Saw a couple dog walkers out there and I also saw two deer, one fox and three rabbits, basically the whole food chain was kicking about.

16min [4min] 12min [3min] 8min [2min].

Hounds session with a much reduced group, just myself Nixon, Rimicans and a 2.19 marathon guy (called Ewan I think?). Anyways it started fairly spicy for my liking but it was either go with them or solo it so I just tucked in. Didn't feel like too hard work but aye defo not comfy, legs felt good which helped matters. Paces 3.19s, 18s, 14s. So yea pretty fast for me!

Seat. So slippy and wet and dark and very misty! Couldn't see my feet at the top of the seat which was exciting and nearly fell over lots of times but held it together. Met maximilian at the end which was lovely. Exams done now so time for Christmas!
Elliptical. Got rather sweaty.
Hermitage with maximilian. Very damp out there.

Merry Christmas all!

5 * purkos to work up a good appetite for the day ahead :)))

Chile pfh ;) Nice early and quite icy one with Rodrigo and Max. Feeling a bit shit after yesterday, not too full but did properly overdo it on the choccy and sweets. Anyways I ran pre brekky so was feeling somewhat normal by the end lol. We do love a good pfh, can't wait to have Mr Wilson back in action for them.
Slap starting in the dark and finishing in the light. All very pleasant.
Joggo in the Hermitage. Spudingtons feeling not so good after helping out at Callander Park all day. Hopefully better for some trossachs fun tomorrow.
private note: A right achilles pop? Maybe, need to see in the morning!

description: Ah yes injury time, love to see it. Calf/ achilles gave a little pop on last nights run, probably from standing about all day and starting the run fairly cold. Was pretty okay jogging this morning, no pain but can't be sacked risking it. Good news is I did a similar thing in summer 2019 but way worse and that took ~1week to heal, so probs just on the XT life for the rest of 2021, back on the miles in 2022!
On the elliptical. Can I do enough XT over the next few days to watch the new season of team ingebrigtsen, we shall see!

25.09 km (23.4 kph) +487m.

Seat4. First 3 laps with peds, had a bit of fun riding on KF on one of the laps and we had not so much fun in the headwind at the top. However it was stupidly warm out there which made things quite pleasant.

Elliptical. Quite content with just the tunes in today. Did 30mins tempo/raz ting which ended up with me very sweaty but felt like some good work, so happy enough. No peep from the calf, could run right now but will leave it till Saturday.  #sensiblespud...

9.44 km (24.6 kph) +150m.

Went out with full intentions to do at least an hour but the crank started falling off so I came home. No bad thing tbh, back to usual tomorrow.
Core mittem Pedley. A good end to the year.
